##  Objective
Build a **binary classification model** to predict whether a patient is at risk of heart disease based on clinical health indicators.

The model takes 13 patient features (age, blood pressure, cholesterol, etc.) as input and outputs:
- `1` → Patient likely has Heart Disease
- `0` → Patient likely does NOT have Heart Disease

---

##  Dataset

| Property | Detail |
|:---|:---|
| **Name** | UCI Heart Disease Dataset |
| **File** | `heart.csv` ← included in this folder |
| **Source** | [Kaggle — Heart Disease UCI](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/ronitf/heart-disease-uci) |
| **Total Patients** | 303 |
| **Features** | 13 clinical features |
| **Target** | Binary — `1` = Disease, `0` = No Disease |
| **Class Balance** | ~52% positive — well balanced ✅ |
| **Missing Values** | None (or filled with column median) |

### Feature Description

| Feature | Description | Type |
|:---|:---|:---:|
| `age` | Patient age in years | Numeric |
| `sex` | Sex — 1 = Male, 0 = Female | Binary |
| `cp` | Chest pain type (1=Typical, 2=Atypical, 3=Non-anginal, 4=Asymptomatic) | Categorical |
| `trestbps` | Resting blood pressure (mmHg) | Numeric |
| `chol` | Serum cholesterol (mg/dl) | Numeric |
| `fbs` | Fasting blood sugar > 120 mg/dl — 1=True, 0=False | Binary |
| `restecg` | Resting ECG results (0, 1, 2) | Categorical |
| `thalach` | Maximum heart rate achieved (bpm) | Numeric |
| `exang` | Exercise induced angina — 1=Yes, 0=No | Binary |
| `oldpeak` | ST depression induced by exercise | Numeric |
| `slope` | Slope of peak exercise ST segment (1, 2, 3) | Categorical |
| `ca` | Number of major vessels blocked (0–3) | Numeric |
| `thal` | Thalassemia type (3=Normal, 6=Fixed, 7=Reversible) | Categorical |
| `target` | **Heart Disease — 1=Yes, 0=No** ← Predict this | Binary |

