## 📊 Key Results & Findings

### Model Performance Summary

| Metric | Logistic Regression | Decision Tree | Random Forest |
|:---|:---:|:---:|:---:|
| **Test Accuracy** | ~85% | ~79% | ~88% |
| **ROC-AUC Score** | ~0.91 | ~0.84 | ~0.94 |
| **CV Accuracy (5-fold)** | ~84% | ~78% | ~87% |

> **ROC-AUC** = 1.0 is perfect · Above 0.90 is excellent for medical classification

### Feature Importance (Random Forest)

| Rank | Feature | Clinical Meaning |
|:---:|:---|:---|
| 🥇 1 | `cp` — Chest Pain Type | Asymptomatic chest pain = highest risk |
| 🥈 2 | `thalach` — Max Heart Rate | Lower max HR = higher disease risk |
| 🥉 3 | `oldpeak` — ST Depression | Higher values = worse cardiac outcome |
| 4 | `ca` — Blocked Vessels | More blockages = more disease risk |
| 5 | `thal` — Thalassemia Type | Abnormal type is key clinical indicator |

### Key Observations

- ✅ **Random Forest** achieved the best overall performance (Accuracy ~88%, AUC ~0.94)
- 📌 **Chest pain type** is the single most predictive feature — counterintuitively, **asymptomatic** pain (type 4) is most dangerous
- 📌 **Age alone is NOT the strongest predictor** — clinical indicators carry more weight
- 📌 **Lower maximum heart rate** significantly increases disease risk
- 📌 Dataset is well-balanced — no class imbalance correction needed
- 🏥 **Logistic Regression** recommended for clinical settings — most interpretable to doctors
- ⚠️ False Negatives (missed disease cases) are more dangerous than False Positives in medical context

